Perform a statistical test for the following:¶

Whether the average response time across complaint types is similar or not (overall)
Are the type of complaint or service requested and location related?

Whether the average response time across complaint types is similar or not (overall)¶

In [335]:
complaint_type=df['Complaint Type'].value_counts().index
for i in range(len(complaint_type)):
    exec("sample{}=df.loc[(df['Complaint Type']=='{}'),'Request_Closing_Time_secs']".format(i+1,complaint_type[i]))

Null hypothesis:H0:There is no significant difference in average resposne time across different complaints Alternate Hypothesis:H1:There is significant difference in average resposne time across different complaints Assumed P value:0.05-Using one way ANOVA test

In [336]:
import scipy.stats as stats
In [337]:
fscore,pvalue=stats.f_oneway(sample1,sample2,sample3,sample4,sample5,sample6,sample7,sample8,sample9,sample10,sample11,sample12)
print("fscore:{:.2f},pvalue:{:.2f}".format(fscore,pvalue))

fscore:860.23,pvalue:0.00

We reject null hypothesis: There is significant difference in average respose time across different complaint types

the average response time across complaint types is not similar (overall)

Are the type of complaint or service requested and location related?¶

Null hypothesis:H0:There is no significant relation between type of complaint and location Alternate Hypothesis:H1:There is some relation between type of complaint and location

Assumed P value:0.05-Using Chi square test

In [342]:
chi_sq_complaint_location_type=pd.crosstab(df['Complaint Type'],df['Location'])
In [343]:
chisq,pval,df,et=stats.chi2_contingency(chi_sq_complaint_location_type)
print("Chisq Score:{:.2f},pvalue:{:.3f}".format(chisq,pval))

Chisq Score:3104085.04,pvalue:0.000

Pvalue(0.00)<alpha value(0.05)

-Hence we reject null hypothesis:H0: -There is some relation between type of complaint and location
